LICENSE

HOWTO

Suppose you have these servers:
  - gitosis.example.com
  - gitlab.example.com
  - gitosis2gitlab.example.com

On gitlab.example.com:
  - rsync over repos
      rsync -avzP gitosis.example.com:~git/repositories/ ~/repositories/
  - create an 'imported' group in Gitlab
  - reorganize repos in imported dir
      mkdir -p /var/opt/gitlab/git-data/repositories/imported

  - add a user for the proxy
  - add SSH pubkey for proxy user


On gitosis2gitlab.example.com:
  - Keep server SSH keys the same
  - Add git user
  - Create configuration file
  - Add SSH privkey for proxy user
  - Create authorized_keys
